latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Giorgio Armani Women’s Fall/Winter 2025-26 Fashion Show.

Giorgio Armani reconnects with his roots, reaﬃrming an authentic style that continuously evolves while drawing from its own essence, yet remains firmly anchored in reality. This is a story where purity and precision of line melt with eﬀortless elegance, embracing the essence of Armani style.

#mfw

Giorgio Armani Men’s Fall Winter 2025-26 Fashion Show.

Elegance to live in. And a way of experiencing elegance free from constraints and impositions, fuelled by individuality. The Giorgio Armani Fall Winter 2025-26 Collection presents the image of a man unafraid to embrace his individuality and gently challenge conventions, wearing garments as an exploration of possibilities rather than a pre-packaged formula. A modern, disenchanted attitude confidently blends formal and informal with passion and ease, confirming the image of an elegant man unaffected from boundaries, powered by a sense of self.

Sensing a widespread need for serenity and constantly seeking a calm and intimate quality, the #GiorgioAramniPrivé Fall Winter 2024-25 Collection is built around pearls. 
Serene in their beauty, pearls are historically associated with the moon, water, wisdom, purity and love. 
Women are dressed in sculpted jackets with powerful shoulders and flowing trousers, with wrap-around overcoats, liquid tops and skirts, or in long dresses that trace the figure and allow each trembling, delicate movement of the body to be perfectly perceived.
The lightest touch. Watch the Giorgio Armani SS25 Men’s Fashion Show

Winter Flowers. The Giorgio Armani Women’s Fall Winter 2024-25 Collection transmits a message of grace and hope, intertwined with the power and energy of nature and the life cycle of our planet. 
Flowers that bloom even in the depths of winter, heralding beauty and regrowth, adorn the garments in this Collection, emphasising their airy, fluid forms and the sense of harmonious elegance that underpins the essence of Giorgio Armani’s work.

Haute Couture en Jeu. 
The #GiorgioArmaniPrivé Spring Summer 2024 Collection represents a play and a moment of suspended evasion. 
In true Armani style, the Collection takes inspiration from the different cultures, from West to East, representing the dream of a woman who is influenced by every place she visits. 
A blend of exquisite aqueous, pale and soft tones – is illuminated by the sparkle of embroidery, creating a playful yet light fashion.

The Look.
The Giorgio Armani Men’s Fall Winter 2024-25 Collection is a reinterpretation of the classic Armani style revisited with a contemporary key. Jackets are larger, fits are more relaxed, to accompany the men’s  movements and to give ethereal vibes. The key of the Collection is simplicity, creating classic yet effective looks, suitable from day to night, and year on year

The Giorgio Armani Spring Summer 2024 Women’s show is about vibrations: they run across entire surfaces in undulating movements and rippling weaves, they expand the chromatic scale to touch notes of bronze and silver and light up in precious greens and purples, only to arrive at a white that permeates the evenings.

Le temps des roses: the #GiorgioArmaniPrivé Fall Winter 2023-24 Collection is a carnal, seductive, mysterious bloom of red roses. Glossy, lacquered roses, embossed on surfaces in a pattern adorned with graphic black and brilliant accents of gold. A journey from West to East through elongated silhouettes, in a collection that reinterprets the most iconic of flowers without resorting to trite romanticism.

Cipria: Giorgio Armani Women’s Fall Winter Collection 2023-24. Make-up (Cipria, as in compact powder, the namesake of the collection) is always an intimate, personal moment, just like the atmosphere that pervades this collection: the wardrobe is fluid and sublime. Shapes follow the body and its movements: silky dresses that recall pyjamas, enveloping shawls, soft trousers, pullovers, elongated jackets, and long dresses, in a cosmetic palette of earth, bronze, and powder with touches of mandarin enhanced by an abundance of black kajal. The stylised flower motif is recurrent, a synthesis of grace, delicacy, and discretion. This interior story is accompanied by subtle plays of shiny and matte that range from clothes to accessories, equally soft, including the new model of La Prima. Beaded fringes dance on berets, almost resembling sparkling hairstyles and adding allure and mystery. An enveloping and personal vision that suggests intimacy as an antidote to a moment of theatrical excess.

The Rondò Armaniano #GiorgioArmaniPrivé Spring Summer 23 collection is an imaginary dance, composed of lines, light and colours that vibrate delicately, as if refracted through a prism. This collection is a luminescent fantasy in which the clothes dance and shine. Small, jewelled jackets, long skirts, fluid trousers and sheath dresses that create seductive silhouettes. Diamond motifs inspired by a painting of Harlequin punctuate the surfaces with colourful geometries in peony pink, turquoise, emerald green and royal blue.

An escape to Mykonos with #GiorgioArmaniMare

latestPosts.caption:
Estate by Giorgio Armani & Kith

Our first summer collection celebrates the heritage of Giorgio Armani through Kith’s lens by traveling from the U.S. to Italy. 

To commemorate the collection, there are special activations in four cities that served as the inspiration for this year’s collection. These activations start with an early release at Kith Malibu, tomorrow, July 4th and a special takeover at the Kith & Giorgio Armani Hamptons House which will open this Saturday, July 5th at the Topping Rose Hotel in Bridgehampton, NY.

The global launch will take place next Thursday, July 10th at Giorgio Armani and Kith stores as well as Armani.com, Kith.com, CA.Kith.com, EU.Kith.com and the Kith App.

Lastly, the collection will be launched with special pop-ups in Beijing, China and Tokyo, Japan on July 10th.

Estate by Giorgio Armani & Kith.

Our first summer collection celebrates the heritage of Giorgio Armani through Kith’s lens by traveling from the U.S. to Italy. 

The name of our collection serves as a double entendre, bridging not only the languages of our home countries, but also our shared vision of an aspirational summer lifestyle. In English, it conjures the grandeur of a luxurious home; in Italian, it simply means “summer.”

We’ll be hosting activations in four cities that inspired our collection, including early launches this weekend at Kith Malibu and the opening of the Giorgio Armani & Kith Hamptons House, followed by the global launch and beach club takeovers at Giorgio Armani’s stores in Forte dei Marmi and Porto Cervo. Stay tuned for more info. 

The full campaign is now live on Armani.com & Kith.com.
